message.reasoning_content:
The user is asking me to respond to a survey as a primary or secondary school teacher from Denmark. I need to respond to 10 statements about AI in education with one of these options: "Strongly disagree", "Disagree", "Agree", "Strongly agree", or "I don't know".

Let me think about reasonable responses from the perspective of a Danish teacher who would likely have a balanced, thoughtful view of AI in education:

TT4G35A - Helps write/improve lesson plans: Agree - This is a well-documented capability of AI
TT4G35B - Adapt learning material to different abilities: Agree - AI can personalize content
TT4G35C - Support students individually: Agree - AI can provide individualized support
TT4G35D - Support specific needs (multilingual, SEN): Agree - AI has shown promise here
TT4G35E - Automate administrative tasks: Strongly agree - This is clearly a major benefit
TT4G35F - Enable misrepresentation/plagiarism: Strongly agree - This is a real concern
TT4G35G - Make inappropriate/incorrect recommendations: Agree - AI can make mistakes
TT4G35H - Amplify biases: Agree - This is a known issue with AI
TT4G35I - Jeopardize privacy/security: Agree - Valid concern about data
TT4G35J - Suggest unsuitable pedagogical approaches: Disagree - This seems like an overstatement, though it could happen

I'll provide balanced responses that reflect both the benefits and concerns of AI in education.
